description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to expand our current nursing Bank team and would like to hear from enthusiastic and committed nurses to join busy wards at Scunthorpe General Hospital, Diana Princess of Wales Hospital and Goole District Hospital Applicants should hold 1st level registration and, like the rest of our nursing team, demonstrate motivation towards delivering the highest standard of nursing care and the ability to work as part of a multi disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust gives Nursing and Midwifery staff on the bank the option to be paid weekly, if you are interested in weekly pay, you will be given further details part of your recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should already hold their NMC PIN Number. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are newly qualified and wish to join the Bank you will be able to join as a Senior Healthcare Assistant for the first 6 months.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are already working within the Trust and would like to join the Bank please contact the Recruitment Team. directly, please don’t apply through NHS Jobs or Healthjobs UK.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Interview Date: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Clark, Head of E-Rostering &amp; Bank Services, Medical Rostering on 03033 305567&lt;/p&gt;
